<Layout title="Terms & Conditions | Jake Fixes Tech LLC"
description="Terms and Conditions for Jake Fixes Tech LLC tech repair and web design services. Read before using our services.">

  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" width="1920" height="1080" fetchpriority="high" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">Legal</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-top:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;max-width:42rem;margin:0 auto;">Please read these terms carefully before using our services.</p>
      <p style="color:#93c5fd;font-size:0.875rem;margin-top:0.75rem;">Last updated: April 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="background:white;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">

      <div class="terms-section">
        <p>These Terms and Conditions ("Agreement") govern your use of the services provided by Jake Fixes Tech LLC, a limited liability company organized under the laws of the State of New Hampshire. By using our services you agree to be bound by this Agreement in its entirety. If you do not agree, do not use our services.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- PART 1 -->
      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;color:#2563eb;border-bottom:2px solid #dbeafe;padding-bottom:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Part 1 — Tech Repair Services</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>By bringing your device to Jake Fixes Tech LLC, scheduling a service appointment, or authorizing any repair work — whether in person, by phone, by text or by email — you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. Your authorization to proceed with a repair constitutes acceptance of this Agreement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>2. Diagnostic Fee</h2>
        <p>A non-refundable diagnostic fee of <strong>$50</strong> is charged for all repair assessments. This fee covers the time and expertise required to evaluate your device. If you choose to proceed with the recommended repair, the $50 diagnostic fee will be credited toward your total repair cost. If you decline the repair after diagnosis, the diagnostic fee is retained in full as payment for services rendered. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>3. Pricing & Payment</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC charges flat-rate pricing for all repair services. All labor fees are due and payable before repair work begins. Parts and components required for a repair are charged separately and will be communicated to you in advance before any parts are ordered or installed. We accept cash, credit/debit card and other payment methods agreed upon in writing.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>All sales are final once work has begun.</strong> No refunds will be issued for completed labor. If you are dissatisfied with a repair, your sole remedy is the 30-day labor warranty described in Section 5.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Chargebacks:</strong> Initiating a chargeback or payment dispute for services legitimately rendered is a breach of this Agreement. Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to pursue collection of any disputed amount, plus associated fees and costs, through all available legal remedies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>4. Data Loss & Backup Responsibility</h2>
        <p><strong>You are solely responsible for backing up all data on your device before submitting it for any service.</strong> Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any data loss, corruption or inaccessibility that occurs during or as a result of the repair process — regardless of cause.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">By leaving your device with us, you acknowledge and accept that data loss is an inherent risk of repair work, and you release Jake Fixes Tech LLC, its owner and agents from any and all liability related to lost, corrupted, deleted or otherwise inaccessible data. This release applies even if data loss results from technician error.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If data backup or recovery services are requested, they will be quoted and billed separately.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>5. Labor Warranty</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC offers a <strong>30-day warranty on labor</strong> for all completed repairs. If the exact same issue that was repaired recurs within 30 calendar days of the completed repair date, we will re-address it at no additional labor charge.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">This warranty is limited to labor only and expressly does not cover:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>New, different or unrelated issues that arise after the repair</li>
          <li>Physical, liquid or accidental damage caused by the customer after pickup</li>
          <li>Software issues, viruses, malware or operating system problems unrelated to the original repair</li>
          <li>Defective or failed third-party replacement parts (subject to the parts manufacturer's own warranty, if any)</li>
          <li>Damage caused by customer modification, tampering or attempted self-repair after service</li>
          <li>Normal wear and tear</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Warranty service must be requested within the 30-day window and is void if the device has been tampered with, modified or serviced by any other party after the original repair.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>6. Parts & Components</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC uses quality third-party replacement parts where original manufacturer (OEM) parts are unavailable or cost-prohibitive. Third-party parts are provided "as-is" and are subject only to the warranty provided by the parts manufacturer, if any. Jake Fixes Tech LLC makes no independent warranty on third-party parts.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">OEM parts can be sourced upon request and may affect pricing and turnaround time. The use of third-party parts may affect manufacturer warranties on your device. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any impact on existing manufacturer warranties.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>7. Device Condition & Pre-Existing Damage</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC will document the visible condition of your device at intake. We are not responsible for any pre-existing damage, defects or issues that are unrelated to the service being performed. Documentation of pre-existing damage will be communicated to you before work begins.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Some repairs carry an inherent risk of additional damage to fragile or aging components. In cases where such risk exists, Jake Fixes Tech LLC will inform you before proceeding. By authorizing work to continue you accept that risk.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Devices repaired as-is:</strong> In some cases, a device may be in a condition where repair carries significant risk (e.g., heavily corroded boards, brittle plastics). If you choose to proceed with service on an as-is device, Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not liable for any damage that occurs as a direct result of the device's pre-existing fragile or compromised condition.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>8. Abandoned Devices</h2>
        <p>Devices not picked up within <strong>30 calendar days</strong> of completion or notification of completion will be considered abandoned property. Jake Fixes Tech LLC will make at least two reasonable attempts to contact you using the contact information provided before treating a device as abandoned.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Abandoned devices may be disposed of, disassembled, repurposed or resold at the sole discretion of Jake Fixes Tech LLC to recover unpaid labor and parts costs. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not liable for any loss of data, software or hardware contained in an abandoned device.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If you are unable to pick up your device within 30 days, please contact us to make alternate arrangements.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>9. Right to Refuse or Discontinue Service</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to refuse service to any individual or for any device at our sole discretion, without explanation. We also reserve the right to stop work at any time if unforeseen complications, safety concerns or ethical concerns arise during a repair. If work is stopped before completion, you will be charged only for the work completed to that point, and your device will be returned to you.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>10. Limitation of Liability — Repairs</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Jake Fixes Tech LLC's total liability to you for any claim arising out of or related to repair services shall not exceed the total amount you paid for the specific service giving rise to the claim.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, punitive or exemplary damages of any kind, including but not limited to loss of data, loss of business, loss of revenue, loss of profits or cost of replacement devices, even if Jake Fixes Tech LLC has been advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>11. On-Site Tech Support</h2>
        <p>On-site service is billed at an hourly rate communicated and agreed upon before the visit. A minimum charge of one hour applies to all on-site visits. Travel time may be included in the hourly rate depending on distance and will be disclosed in advance. Payment for on-site visits is due upon completion of the service call. Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to require a deposit before scheduling on-site visits.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- PART 2 -->
      <div class="terms-section" id="web-services-terms">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;color:#2563eb;border-bottom:2px solid #dbeafe;padding-bottom:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Part 2 — Web Design & Management Services</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>12. Agreement to Web Services Terms</h2>
        <p>By engaging Jake Fixes Tech LLC for any web design, development or management service — including by paying a deposit, signing a proposal or authorizing work to begin — you agree to the terms in this section in addition to the general terms above. These terms apply to all website build packages, management plans and on-demand hourly work.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>13. Web Services Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>All website build projects require a <strong>50% non-refundable deposit</strong> before work begins. The deposit is non-refundable regardless of whether the project is completed, as it compensates Jake Fixes Tech LLC for time, planning and resources committed to your project. The remaining 50% is due upon completion and before the website is launched or any deliverables are handed over.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If final payment is not received within <strong>14 calendar days</strong> of project completion, Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to withhold delivery of all files, assets and access until payment is received in full. Interest may accrue on overdue balances at a rate of 1.5% per month.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">On-demand hourly work is billed in <strong>1-hour minimums</strong>. Invoices for hourly work are due within <strong>14 calendar days</strong> of the invoice date. Late payment may result in work being paused until the balance is cleared. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any delays or consequences resulting from a work pause due to non-payment.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Chargebacks:</strong> Initiating a chargeback for web services legitimately rendered is a breach of this Agreement. Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to pursue full recovery of any disputed amounts plus fees through all available legal remedies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>14. Project Scope & Revisions</h2>
        <p>Each build package includes a defined number of revision rounds as stated on the Web Services page and confirmed at project start. A revision round is defined as a single, consolidated set of changes submitted at one time via written communication. Multiple separate submissions do not constitute a single revision round.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Additional revisions beyond the included rounds are billed at <strong>$75/hour</strong> with a one-hour minimum. Any requests that fall outside the originally agreed scope — including additional pages, new features, substantial redesigns or major content restructuring — are out-of-scope and will be quoted and billed separately before work proceeds.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Jake Fixes Tech LLC will not begin out-of-scope work without written confirmation of approval from the client.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>15. Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>The client is responsible for providing all content required for the website in a timely manner, including but not limited to: written copy, images, logos, brand guidelines, colors, fonts and any third-party credentials or integrations needed for the build. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for sourcing, writing or acquiring client content unless separately agreed upon in writing.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If the client does not respond to requests for content, feedback or approval within <strong>7 calendar days</strong>, the project will be paused. Projects paused for more than <strong>30 calendar days</strong> due to client inaction may be subject to a project restart fee. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any timeline delays caused by client inaction.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">The client is responsible for ensuring that all content provided to Jake Fixes Tech LLC does not infringe on any third-party copyright, trademark or other intellectual property rights. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not liable for any legal claims arising from client-provided content.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>16. Project Timeline</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC will provide an estimated project timeline at the start of each engagement. All timelines are good-faith estimates and are not guarantees of delivery. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not liable for delays caused by client inaction, late content delivery, change requests or circumstances outside our reasonable control including third-party service outages, illness or force majeure events.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>17. Website Ownership & Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>Upon receipt of <strong>full and final payment</strong>, the client owns their completed website including all custom code, design assets and content created specifically for their project. Jake Fixes Tech LLC retains no ownership claim over the delivered work after final payment is received.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Until final payment is received in full</strong>, all website code, designs, mockups and related assets remain the exclusive intellectual property of Jake Fixes Tech LLC. The client has no right to use, publish, transfer or build upon any deliverables until payment is complete.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Portfolio use:</strong> Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to display completed websites in a portfolio, on social media or as examples of work for marketing purposes. If the client wishes to opt out of portfolio display, they must submit a written request before project completion. Portfolio display rights survive payment and termination of this Agreement.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Third-party tools, frameworks, fonts or libraries used in the project are subject to their own respective licenses, which are not transferred as part of this Agreement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>18. Domain & Hosting</h2>
        <p>Where Jake Fixes Tech LLC registers a domain on behalf of a client, the domain will be registered in the client's name and transferred to the client's control upon final payment. Clients are responsible for renewing their own domain names unless enrolled in a management plan that explicitly includes domain renewal services.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Jake Fixes Tech LLC uses Cloudflare Pages for website hosting. Hosting through Cloudflare Pages is provided at no additional cost as part of the build. Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any service disruptions, downtime or changes to Cloudflare's platform or pricing. If Cloudflare modifies or discontinues free hosting, Jake Fixes Tech LLC will notify affected clients but is not obligated to absorb any resulting costs.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If a client cancels a management plan, their website will remain live on Cloudflare Pages under their own account. Jake Fixes Tech LLC will cease all management activities at the end of the final paid billing period.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>19. Management Plan Terms & Cancellation Policy</h2>
        <p>Management plans are optional recurring services separate from the one-time build fee. Plans renew automatically unless cancelled. Pricing is as follows:</p>

